SIMPLE: soporific
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soporific
<hw>Sop`o*rif"ic</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sopor</ets> a heavy sleep (akin to <ets>somnus</ets> sleep) +
<ets>facere</ets> to make. See <er>Somnolent</er>, <er>Fact</er>.]</ety>
<def>Causing sleep; tending to cause sleep; soporiferous; <as>as, the
<ex>soporific</ex> virtues of opium</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Somniferous; narcotic; opiate; anodyne.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soporific</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Soporific
<hw>Sop`o*rif"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A medicine, drug, plant, or
other agent that has the quality of inducing sleep; a
narcotic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soporous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Soporose</ent>⟦br⟧
